The '''Industrial Heritage Trail''' ({{lang-de|Route der Industriekultur}}) links tourist attractions related to the [[industrial heritage]] in the [[Ruhr area]] in [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.route-industriekultur.de/menue/menue.html&lang=2 | title = What is the Industrial Heritage Trail? | accessdate=2009-05-02}}</ref> It is a part of the [[European Route of Industrial Heritage]].
==The route== The trail network connects museums and exhibitions that present the industrial revolution during the last 750 years in the Ruhr area. It includes 400&nbsp;km of road network and about 700&nbsp;km of bicycle tracks.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ruhr2010.de/en/ruhr-metropolis/visiting-the-ruhr-metropolis/routes.html | title = Routes | accessdate=2009-05-02}}</ref>
==The attractions== There are 52 main attractions on the trail. * [[Bochum Dahlhausen Railway Museum]] * [[German Inland Waterways Museum]] * [[Villa Hügel]] * [[Zeche Carl]]
